<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Y. Zhong" authorityYear="1991" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium ecalcaratum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ecalcaratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Epimedium ecalcaratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Baoxing, Luding, Shimian and Pengxian, Sichuan, often on mountain slopes and grassland with elevations ranging from 1100 m to 2100 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Y. Zhong" authorityYear="1991" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium ecalcaratum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ecalcaratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Epimedium ecalcaratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers from April to May, and fruits from May to August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
